1. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with stochastic optimal control problem for systems, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses input-output experimental data to identify the trajectory-dependent linearized system, which involves machine learning techniques. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a controller design for systems with unknown dynamics, which can be considered as an application of artificial intelligence. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): Although the paper does not explicitly mention the use of neural or evolutionary computing techniques, the proposed approach of identifying the linearized system from experimental data can be related to these sub-fields. 
5. cs.SI (Signal and Image Processing): The impulse responses of the nominal system used in the paper can be considered as signals, and the identification of the linearized system can be related to signal processing techniques.
